vo Hern\u00e1ndez\n| [[Uruguay]]\n|\n|-\n\n| 2011\n| ''[[Silent House (2011 film)|Silent House]]''\n| 87 min.\n| [[Chris Kentis]], Laura Lau\n|[[United States]]\n|\n|-\n\n| 2014\n| ''[[Birdman (film)|Birdman]]''\n| 119 min.\n| [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu|Alejandro G. I\u00f1\u00e1rritu]]\n|[[M\u00e9xico]]\n|\n|-\n\n| 2015\n| ''[[Hardcore Henry]]''\n| 96 min.\n| [[Ilya Naishuller]]\n|[[Russia]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |first=Bryan |last=Bishop |url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/3/16/11248318/hardcore-henry-gopro-movie-director-interview-sxsw-2016 |title=The making of Hardcore Henry, the craziest first-person action movie you'll ever see |work=[[The Verge]] |date=March 16, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|\"[[eps3.4_runtime-error.r00]]\" (''[[Mr. Robot]]'')\n| 43 min. (TV episode)\n|[[Sam Esmail]]\n|[[United States]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/was-that-mr-robot-episode-really-shot-in-one-take-eps34_runtime-err0rr00-is-the-most-ambitious-hour-of-the-series-so-far-3246974 |title=Was That 'Mr. Robot' Episode Really Shot In One Take? \"eps3.4_runtime-err0r.r00\" Is The Most Ambitious Hour Of The Series So Far |last=O'Keeffe |first=Jack |date=2017-11-09 |work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |publisher= |access-date=2017-12-27 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n|''[[Bushwick (film)|Bushwick]]''\n| 94 min.\n|[[Cary Murnion]], [[Jonathan Milott]]\n|[[United States]]\n|\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2018\n|[[The Haunting of Hill House (TV series)|\"Two Storms\" (''The Haunting of Hill House'' ep. 1.6)]]\n| 57 min. (TV episode)\n| [[Mike Flanagan (filmmaker)|Mike Flanagan]]\n|[[United States]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Evangelista |first1=Chris |title=Here\u2019s How \u2018The Haunting of Hill House\u2019 Episode 6 Was Made |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/haunting-of-hill-house-episode-6/ |website=[[/Film]] |date=October 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite mag |last1=Stack |first1=Tim |title=The Haunting of Hill House creator Mike Flanagan on hidden clues, major scares, and a season 2 |url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/10/23/the-haunting-of-hill-house-mike-flanagan-post-mortem/ |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]] |date=October 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2019\n|''[[1917 (2019 film)|1917]]''\n| 118 min.\n|[[Sam Mendes]]\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|\n|}\n\n===Works other than film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Notes\n! {{tooltip|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Tony Hinchcliffe: One Shot]]''\n| [[Comedy Special]] \n| <ref>{{Citation|title=Tony Hinchcliffe: One Shot|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt5378728/|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[God of War (2018 video game)|God of War]]''\n| [[Action-adventure game]]\n| <ref>{{cite news|last1=Bratt|first1=Chris|title=God of War director explains why entire game has no camera cuts|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-06-21-god-of-war-director-explains-why-the-entire-game-has-no-camera-cuts|accessdate=13 April 2018|work=Eurogamer.net|date=21 June 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of one shot music videos]]\n* [[Long take]]\n* [[Digital cinematography]]\n* [[Digital cinema]]\n* [[List of films shot on digital video prior to 2015]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Cinematic techniques}}\n{{Film genres}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:One shot (movie)}}\n[[Category:Cinematic techniques]]\n[[Category:Film and video technology]]\n[[Category:Digital movie cameras]]\n", "text_old": "A '''one-shot''' or '''continuous shot feature film''' is a full-length movie filmed in one [[long take]] by a single camera, or manufactured to give the impression it was.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://feenta.com/best-one-shot-one-take-movies/ |title=Best one shot (one-take) movies |last= |first= |date=2016-09-25 |website=FEENTA |publisher= |access-date=2018-03-21 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n== Examples ==\n\n=== Actual \"one shot\" ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Leng