le-1.351752 |title=A movie shot in real time recalls Colombian nightmare |last=Beale |first=Lewis |date=2008-07-15 |website=NY Daily News |publisher= |access-date=2018-04-21 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Still Orangutans]]'\n|81 min.\n|[[Gustavo Spolidero]]\n| [[Brazil]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/still-orangutans-125777|title=Still Orangutans|work=The Hollywood Reporter|agency=AP|author=Lowe, Justin|date=2008-11-12|access-date=2018-04-21 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| 2011\n| ''[[21 Brothers]]''\n| 96 min. \n| [[Michael McGuire (director)|Michael McGuire]]\n| [[Canada]]\n|\n|-\n\n| rowspan=4|2013\n| ''[[Rati Chakravyuh]]''\n| 102 min.\n| [[Ashish Avikunthak]]\n| [[India]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.artslant.com/ind/articles/show/40024 |title=Circling Time |last=Sorabjee |first=Deepika |date=2014-07-06 |website=ArtSlant |publisher= |access-date=2015-10-07 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| ''[[Fish & Cat]]''\n| 134 min.\n| [[Shahram Mokri]]\n| [[Iran]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2013/film/global/venice-film-review-fish-cat-1200615586/ |title=Venice Film Review: 'Fish & Cat' |last=Simon |first=Alissa |date=2013-09-17 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher= |access-date=2018-04-21 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| ''[[El triste olor de la carne]]''\n| 87 min.\n| [[Crist\u00f3bal Arteaga]]\n| [[Spain]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/sad-smell-flesh-el-triste-583118 |title=The Sad Smell of Flesh (El Triste Olor de la Carne): Karlovy Vary Review |last=Dalton |first=Stephen |date=2013-07-10 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher= |access-date=2016-01-12 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| ''[[Ana Arabia]]''\n| 85 min.\n| [[Amos Gita\u00ef]]\n| [[Israel]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2013/09/venice-review-amos-gitais-shot-in-one-take-ana-arabia-93938/ |title=Venice Review: Amos Gitai's Shot-In-One-Take 'Ana Arabia' |last=Lyttelton |first=Oliver |date=2013-09-09 |website=[[IndieWire]] |publisher= |access-date=2015-11-27 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n|2013\n|''Somebody Marry Me''\n|98 min.\n|John Asher\n|United States\n| <ref>{{cite web |title= Malibu local completes film |url=http://www.malibutimes.com/malibu_life/article_70b2fada-d88b-11e2-bfb7-001a4bcf887a.html |website=The Malibu Times |date=2013-06-13 |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| 2014\n| ''[[Agadam]]''\n| 123 min.\n| [[Mohamad Issack]]\n| [[India]]\n| <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/a-record-start/article5530220.ece |title=A record start |last=Jeshi |first=K. |date=2014-01-02 |newspaper=The Hindu |publisher= |access-date=2015-10-20 |quote=}}\n{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/a-record-start/article5530220.ece|title=A record start|first=K.|last=JESHI|publisher=|newspaper=The Hindu|date=2014-01-02}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| rowspan=3|2015\n| ''[[Victoria (2015 film)|Victoria]]''\n| 140 min.\n| [[Sebastian Schipper]]\n| [[Germany]]\n| <ref name=\"victoria1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2015/02/adopt-films-picks-up-one-shot-heist-thriller-victoria-65040/ |title=Adopt Films Picks Up One-Shot Heist Thriller 'Victoria' |last=Kohn |first=Eric |date=2015-02-16 |website=IndieWire |publisher= |access-date=2015-09-27 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| ''Anino sa likod ng buwan''\n| 120 min.\n| [[Jun Lana]]\n| [[Philippines]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.piecsmakow.pl/film.do?lang=en&id=158 |title=Shadow Behind the Moon |last= |first= |date= |website=Five Flavours Film Festival |publisher= |access-date=2017-03-29 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| ''Daksha''\n| \n| [[S. Narayan]]\n| India\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/duniya-vijay-s-daksha-with-s-narayan-news-kannada-oehjBmhigibsi.html |title=Duniya Vijay's 'Daksha' with S.Narayan |last= |first= |date=2014-04-07 |website=Sify Movies |publisher= |access-date=2017-02-21 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| rowspan=3|2016 \n| ''Eight'' \n| 81 min. \n| Peter Blackburn \n| [[Australia]] \n| <ref>{{c